definition.value: a lipase increased AE that is greater than 2.0 - 5.0 times upper limit of normal
a lipase increased AE that is greater than 5.0 times upper limit of normal
a localized edema AE that has localized to dependent areas, no disability or functional impairment
a lung infection AE that has moderate symptoms; oral intervention indicated (e.g., antibiotic, antifungal, antiviral)
a lung infection AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic, endoscopic, or operative intervention indicated
a lymphocyte count decreased AE that is less than the lower limit of normal - 800/mm3; less than the lower limit of normal - 0.8 x 10e9 /L
a lymphocyte count decreased AE that is less than 800 - 500/mm3; less than 0.8 - 0.5 x 10e9 /L
a lymphocyte count decreased AE that is less than 500 - 200/mm3; less than 0.5 - 0.2 x 10e9 /L
a lymphocyte count decreased AE that is less than 200/mm3; less than 0.2 x 10e9 /L
a myocarditis AE that has asymptomatic with laboratory (e.g., BNP [B-Natriuretic Peptide ]) or cardiac imaging abnormalities
a myocarditis AE that has symptoms with mild to moderate activity or exertion
a myocarditis AE that has severe with symptoms at rest or with minimal activity or exertion; intervention indicated
a myocarditis AE that has life-threatening consequences; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., continuous IV therapy or mechanical hemodynamic support)
a neutrophil count decreased AE that is less than the lower limit of normal - 1500/mm3; less than the lower limit of normal - 1.5 x 10e9 /L
a neutrophil count decreased AE that is less than 1500 - 1000/mm3; less than 1.5 - 1.0 x 10e9 /L
a neutrophil count decreased AE that is less than 1000 - 500/mm3; less than 1.0 - 0.5 x 10e9 /L
a neutrophil count decreased AE that is less than 500/mm3; less than 0.5 x 10e9 /L
an esophageal stenosis AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function
an esophageal stenosis AE that has severely altered GI function; tube feeding; hospitalization indicated; elective operative intervention indicated
an esophagitis AE that is symptomatic; altered eating/swallowing; oral supplements indicated
an esophagitis AE that has severely altered eating/swallowing; tube feeding, TPN or hospitalization indicated
an oral cavity fistula AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function
an oral cavity fistula AE that has severely altered GI function; TPN or hospitalization indicated; elective operative intervention indicated
a papilloedema AE that has a symptomatic decline in vision; visual field defect present sparing the central 20 degrees

a papilloedema AE that has blindness (20/200 or worse) in the affected eye
a pericardial effusion AE that has asymptomatic effusion size small to moderate
a pericardial effusion AE that has effusion with physiologic consequences
a portal hypertension AE that has decreased portal vein flow
a portal hypertension AE that has reversal/retrograde portal vein flow; associated with varices and/or ascites

a skin infection AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic or operative intervention indicated

a small intestinal stenosis AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function
a small intestinal stenosis AE that is symptomatic and severely altered GI function; tube feeding, TPN or hospitalization indicated; non-emergent operative intervention indicated
a soft tissue infection AE that is localized; local intervention indicated (e.g., topical antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral)
a soft tissue infection AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic or operative intervention indicated
a gastric hemorrhage AE where transfusion, radiologic, endoscopic, or elective operative intervention indicated
a tracheitis AE that has moderate symptoms; oral intervention indicated (e.g., antibiotic, antifungal, antiviral)
a tracheitis AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic, endoscopic, or operative intervention indicated
an upper gastrointestinal hemorrhage AE where transfusion, radiologic, endoscopic, or elective operative intervention indicated
a urine output decreased AE that has oliguria (less than 80 ml in 8 hr)

a vaginal infection AE that is localized; local intervention indicated (e.g., topical antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral)
